---
/**
 * lsm-compaction-deep-dive · Figure 5 — Level 5 "WHY A TOMBSTONE MUST OUTLIVE
 * EVERY OLDER COPY": older SSTable (value) + newer SSTable (tombstone), the
 * correct "keep tombstone" path vs the "purge too early" resurrection path, plus
 * the DISTRIBUTED / gc_grace_seconds note.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/storage-engines/lsm-compaction-deep-dive.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, marker-end, …).
 *
 * The source page declared its arrowhead markers (#arw / #arwA / #arwG) ONCE in a
 * hidden top-of-body <svg defs>. Because each figure is now an isolated component,
 * the #arwG (fill #2f5d3a) and #arwA (fill #7a1f12) markers this figure references
 * via marker-end="url(#…)" are inlined here in a local <defs> so it resolves
 * standalone (verbatim from the source defs).
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 200"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Tombstone resurrection: an older SSTable still holds the value while a newer SSTable holds the tombstone. If the tombstone is purged before the old SSTable is compacted away, the value reappears with nothing to mask it."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arwA"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#7a1f12"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="280"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">WHY A TOMBSTONE MUST OUTLIVE EVERY OLDER COPY</text
            >
            <!-- old sstable -->
            <rect x="20" y="46" width="150" height="50" rx="8" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
            <text x="95" y="66" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >older SSTable</text
            >
            <text x="95" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#111110"
                >k = "alice" (value)</text
            >
            <!-- new sstable -->
            <rect x="20" y="118" width="150" height="50" rx="8" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="95"
                y="138"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">newer SSTable</text
            >
            <text x="95" y="156" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#9a2417"
                >k = ⌧ tombstone</text
            >
            <!-- correct path -->
            <line x1="172" y1="107" x2="218" y2="107" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"
            ></line>
            <rect x="222" y="44" width="150" height="58" rx="8" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="297"
                y="64"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">✓ keep tombstone</text
            >
            <text x="297" y="80" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#244a2e"
                >until merged past</text
            >
            <text x="297" y="93" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#244a2e"
                >the old copy → read = "not found"</text
            >
            <!-- wrong path -->
            <line
                x1="172"
                y1="140"
                x2="218"
                y2="140"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-dasharray="4 3"
                marker-end="url(#arwA)"></line>
            <rect x="222" y="118" width="150" height="58" rx="8" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="297"
                y="138"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">✗ purge too early</text
            >
            <text x="297" y="154" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#7a2218"
                >old value has no mask</text
            >
            <text x="297" y="167" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#7a2218"
                >→ deleted data RETURNS</text
            >
            <!-- distributed note -->
            <rect
                x="392"
                y="60"
                width="158"
                height="100"
                rx="10"
                fill="#fbfaf2"
                stroke="#1f3a5a"
                stroke-width="1.4"></rect>
            <text
                x="471"
                y="80"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">DISTRIBUTED</text
            >
            <text x="471" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#111110"
                >delete must reach</text
            >
            <text x="471" y="113" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#111110"
                >every replica first</text
            >
            <text
                x="471"
                y="135"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                fill="#9a2417"
                font-weight="700">gc_grace_seconds</text
            >
            <text x="471" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >Cassandra default 10 days</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        A tombstone must outlive <em>every</em> older SSTable still holding the value. Purge it too early
        and the next read finds the old value with nothing to mask it.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
